## Dynamic Programming

Fill grid in-place: first row/column are prefix sums. Each cell is grid[i][j] + min(above, left). Answer is bottom-right.

```js
function minimumPathSum(grid) {
  const m = grid.length, n = grid[0].length;
  for (let i = 1; i < m; i++) grid[i][0] += grid[i-1][0];
  for (let j = 1; j < n; j++) grid[0][j] += grid[0][j-1];
  for (let i = 1; i < m; i++)
    for (let j = 1; j < n; j++)
