## Trie-based Search

Build a Trie from all contacts, storing words at each node. For each prefix of the query, collect all words under that node.

```js
function phoneDirectory(contacts, query) {
  const root = {};
  for (const word of contacts) {
    let node = root;
    for (const ch of word) {
      if (!node[ch]) node[ch] = {};
      if (!node[ch].words) node[ch].words = [];
      node[ch].words.push(word);
      node = node[ch];
    }
  }
  const result = [];
  let node = root;
  for (const ch of query) {
    if (node && node[ch]) {
      node = node[ch];
      result.push([...node.words].sort());
    } else { node = null; result.push([]); }
  }
  return result;
}
```

**Time:** O(n * l + q * n * l)
**Space:** O(n * l)

## Level-by-Level Using Next Pointers

Use established next pointers of the current level to connect nodes at the next level. O(1) extra space since the tree is perfect.

```js
function populatingNextRightPointersInEachNode(root) {
  if (!root) return root;
  let leftmost = root;
  while (leftmost.left) {
    let curr = leftmost;
    while (curr) {
      curr.left.next = curr.right;
      if (curr.next) curr.right.next = curr.next.left;
      curr = curr.next;
    }
    leftmost = leftmost.left;
  }
  return root;
}
```

**Time:** O(n)
**Space:** O(1)

## Bit Manipulation

A power of two has exactly one set bit. n & (n-1) is 0 for powers of two. Ensure n > 0.

```js
function powerOfTwo(n) {
  return n > 0 && (n & (n - 1)) === 0;
}
```

