## Left and Right Products

First pass: prefix products from left. Second pass: multiply by suffix products from right.

```js
function productOfArrayExceptSelf(nums) {
  const n = nums.length, result = new Array(n).fill(1);
  let left = 1;
  for (let i = 0; i < n; i++) { result[i] = left; left *= nums[i]; }
  let right = 1;
  for (let i = n-1; i >= 0; i--) { result[i] *= right; right *= nums[i]; }
  return result;
}
```

**Time:** O(n)
**Space:** O(1) extra

## LSD Radix Sort

For each digit position (units, tens, hundreds...), use counting sort to sort by that digit. Repeat for all digits of the maximum number.

```js
function radixSortDataStructuresAndAlgorithmsTutorials(arr) {
  const max = Math.max(...arr);
  for (let exp = 1; Math.floor(max / exp) > 0; exp *= 10) {
    const output = new Array(arr.length), count = new Array(10).fill(0);
    for (const n of arr) count[Math.floor(n / exp) % 10]++;
    for (let i = 1; i < 10; i++) count[i] += count[i-1];
    for (let i = arr.length-1; i >= 0; i--) {
      const d = Math.floor(arr[i] / exp) % 10;
      output[--count[d]] = arr[i];
    }
    for (let i = 0; i < arr.length; i++) arr[i] = output[i];
  }
  return arr;
}
```

**Time:** O(d * (n + 10)) where d = digits
**Space:** O(n)

